<p>Finally, it turns around and makes a charge at one of the Ilkley Town players who quickly dodges out of the way, sending the spectators into peals of laughter</p>

<p>The video was uploaded to Ilkley Town's Twitter page and has already been watched over half a million times.  </p>

<p>The footage has been the source of amusement for football fans as one wrote: 'Great diagonal run from the alpaca,' and another commented: 'Think he was slightly offside'. </p>

<p>Another Twitter used commented on the rare sight, writing: ' 'I'm used to seeing the odd donkey on the pitch but never an alpaca.'</p>

<p>It's not known how the alpaca broke free to invade the pitch but as one person put it, it's: 'No cause for a-llama!'  </p>
